          <!-- Body -->
          <div class="reveal reveal-delay-1">

            <div class="legal-intro">
              <p>This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>UNI-SERVICES</strong> ("we", "us", "our") collects, uses, and protects information about you when you use our platform — including <strong>UniCare+</strong>, <strong>UniShow</strong>, and <strong>UniSpace</strong> — or contact us through our website.</p>
              <p>By using our services, you agree to the practices described in this policy.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="legal-section" id="collect">
              <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
              <h3>a) Information You Provide</h3>
              <ul>
                <li><strong>Contact Form:</strong> When you reach out to us, we collect your name, email address, subject, and message content.</li>
                <li><strong>Account Registration:</strong> If you create an account, we collect your name, email, and password (stored encrypted).</li>
                <li><strong>UniCare+:</strong> Health-related information you provide for consultations, including symptoms, medical history, and prescriptions. This data is handled with the highest level of care and confidentiality.</li>
                <li><strong>UniShow:</strong> Booking details including seat preferences, event selections, and payment confirmation references.</li>
                <li><strong>UniSpace:</strong> Files and data you upload for storage. This content is encrypted and accessible only to you.</li>
              </ul>
              <h3>b) Automatically Collected</h3>
              <ul>
                <li>Device type, browser, and operating system</li>
                <li>IP address and approximate location (country/city level)</li>
                <li>Pages visited, time spent, and interaction data</li>
                <li>Referral source (how you found us)</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="legal-section" id="use">
              <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
              <ul>
                <li>To respond to your enquiries and provide customer support</li>
                <li>To deliver and improve our services (UniCare+, UniShow, UniSpace)</li>
                <li>To send transactional emails (booking confirmations, receipts)</li>
                <li>To prevent fraud, abuse, and ensure platform security</li>
                <li>To comply with legal obligations</li>
                <li>To analyse usage patterns and improve user experience</li>
              </ul>
              <div class="legal-callout">
                <strong>We do not sell your personal data.</strong> Ever. To anyone.
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="legal-section" id="share">
              <h2>3. Sharing Your Data</h2>
              <p>We do not share your personal data with third parties except in the following limited circumstances:</p>
              <ul>
                <li><strong>Service Providers:</strong> Trusted vendors who help us operate the platform (e.g., cloud infrastructure, email delivery). They are bound by strict data processing agreements.</li>
                <li><strong>UniCare+ Partners:</strong> Healthcare professionals on our platform receive only the information necessary to provide your consultation — never more.</li>
                <li><strong>Legal Requirements:</strong> If required by law, court order, or government authority, we may disclose data as legally compelled.</li>
                <li><strong>Business Transfers:</strong> In the event of a merger or acquisition, your data may transfer to the new entity, subject to the same privacy protections.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="legal-section" id="security">
              <h2>4. Data Security</h2>
              <p>We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your information:</p>
              <ul>
                <li>End-to-end encryption for UniSpace file storage</li>
                <li>Encrypted passwords using bcrypt hashing</li>
                <li>HTTPS enforced across all pages</li>
                <li>Regular security audits and vulnerability assessments</li>
                <li>Access controls — only authorised personnel can access user data</li>
              </ul>
              <p>While we take every precaution, no system is 100% secure. We encourage you to use strong, unique passwords and contact us immediately if you suspect unauthorised access.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="legal-section" id="cookies">
              <h2>5. Cookies &amp; Tracking</h2>
              <p>We use minimal cookies to ensure the platform functions correctly:</p>
              <ul>
                <li><strong>Session Cookies:</strong> To keep you logged in during a session</li>
                <li><strong>Preference Cookies:</strong> To remember your theme (light/dark) and other settings</li>
                <li><strong>Analytics:</strong> Anonymised usage data to understand how users interact with the platform</li>
              </ul>
              <p>You can disable cookies through your browser settings, though some features may not function correctly without them.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="legal-section" id="rights">
              <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
              <p>You have the following rights regarding your personal data:</p>
              <ul>
                <li><strong>Access:</strong> Request a copy of the data we hold about you</li>
                <li><strong>Correction:</strong> Ask us to correct inaccurate data</li>
                <li><strong>Deletion:</strong> Request deletion of your data ("right to be forgotten")</li>
                <li><strong>Portability:</strong> Receive your data in a machine-readable format</li>
                <li><strong>Objection:</strong> Object to how we process your data</li>
              </ul>
              <p>To exercise any of these rights, email us at <a href="mailto:uniservices013@gmail.com">uniservices013@gmail.com</a>. We will respond within 30 days.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="legal-section" id="children">
              <h2>7. Children's Privacy</h2>
              <p>Our services are not directed at children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe a child has provided us with their information, please contact us immediately and we will delete it promptly.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="legal-section" id="changes">
              <h2>8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
              <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will revise the "Effective Date" at the top and, for significant changes, notify users via email or a prominent notice on our platform.</p>
              <p>Continued use of UNI-SERVICES after changes constitutes your acceptance of the updated policy.</p>
            </div>

